29/12/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- At an extraordinary session Wednesday (December 29th), parliament approved a government reshuffle that Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor proposed on Monday. As part of efforts to boost her economic team, Kosor decided to replace four cabinet members. In their place, she appointed Martina Dalic as finance minister, Jasen Mesic as culture minister, Branko Bacic as environment and construction minister, and Davor Bozinovic as defence minister. Domagoj Milosevic will take over the newly created post of deputy prime minister in charge of investments. Kosor says the team's top priorities will be to implement measures aimed at economic recovery and completing EU accession talks. (HRT, Hina, Poslovni Dnevnik - 29/12/10)
